quran[11]{c,v,t,f}:
  100,10,"And that within the breasts is obtained,{1}",footnotes:1:i.e., when all secrets are made known.
  100,11,"Indeed, their Lord with them, that Day, is [fully] Aware.{1}",footnotes:1:Fully acquainted and familiar with everything about each one of them.
  101,7,"He will be in a pleasant life."
  101,8,"But as for one whose scales are light,"
  101,9,"His refuge{1} will be an abyss.{2}",footnotes:1:Literally, "mother" (a man's original refuge) , which will envelop him as in an embrace.i.e., the pit of Hellfire.
  102,4,"Then, no! You are going to know."
  102,5,"No! If you only knew with knowledge of certainty...{1}",footnotes:1:The conclusion of this verse is estimated to be "...you would not have been distracted from preparing for the Hereafter."
  102,6,"You will surely see the Hellfire."
  103,1,"By time,{1}",footnotes:1:An oath in which Allāh swears by time throughout the ages.
  103,2,"Indeed, mankind is in loss,"
  103,3,"Except for those who have believed and done righteous deeds and advised each other to truth and advised each other to patience."